## 2. The Dual-System Mental Model (Critical)

These two systems share infrastructure but have **fundamentally different data models**:

| Aspect | Vacation Rentals / Holiday Homes | Hospitality |
|---|---|---|
| Listing unit | One `vacation_rentals` row | One `hotels` row + many `room_types` |
| Photos | Per listing + per-space (bedroom/bathroom/kitchen) | Per-hotel (categorized) + per-room-type |
| Availability | Per listing (the whole unit is booked) | Per-room-unit (specific physical room) |
| Booking | Books the whole vacation rental | Books one or more units of a room type |
| Pricing | Per listing (4 tiers + seasonal) | Per-room-type (4 tiers + seasonal) |
| Address | Approximate by default | Always precise |
| Host type | Individual or **`vacation_rental_operator`** (مشغّل بيوت عطلات) | Hotel company only |

**When writing code, always ask: "Does this apply to Vacation Rentals, Hospitality, or both?"**
- Both (auth, payments, chat, reviews) → put in shared module
- Vacation Rentals only → prefer `modules/vacation-rentals/` for new Phase 3 work
- Hospitality only → put in `modules/hospitality/`
- Touches both via polymorphism (bookings, search) → handle both branches explicitly

